data.title: Claudiu Keșerü - Wikipedia
data.snippet:
Claudiu Andrei Keșerü (Romanian pronunciation: (/wiki/Help:IPA/Romanian "Help:IPA/Romanian"); born 2 December 1986) is a Romanian former professional footballer who played as a striker#Striker "Forward (association football)").

After starting out at his hometown side Bihor Oradea "FC Bihor Oradea (1958)"), Keșerü soon moved to Nantes in 2003. Over the course of nearly eleven years in France, he represented five clubs and amassed Ligue 1 and Ligue 2 totals of 240 appearances and 67 goals. In 2014, he returned to his native country by signing a contract with defending champions Steaua București. [...] Keșerü went on to score two goals in the second leg home match against FK Žalgiris in the second qualifying round of the 2017–18 UEFA Champions League which Ludogorets won 5–3 on aggregate. Keșerü won the Bulgarian championship for a third time in the 2017–18 "2017–18 First Professional Football League (Bulgaria)") season, also becoming top goalscorer of the league with 26 goals. He also scored the winning goal in the 2018 Bulgarian Supercup final. On 7 October 2018, he contributed three goals in a 4–1 away win over Botev Vratsa, thus becoming the foreigner with the most hat-tricks in the A PFG, having managed the feat on five separate occasions. On 19 September 2019, Keșerü scored three goals in the 5:1 home win against CSKA Moscow in a UEFA Europa League group stage match. In May 2020, [...] | Keșerü with Ludogorets Razgrad in 2019 |

data.snippet:
Claudiu popa
Claudiu Popa | Cybersafety Expert

# Who is Claudiu Popa?

###### Everything to know about Canada’s cybersecurity expert

soundcloud 1024

###### Back Story

## Passion for Canada’s Cybersecurity Standing on the World Stage

With a robust Computer Science degree and top-tier industry certifications in information security, risk management, privacy, and more, he stands as a leading authority in Canada’s cybersecurity sector. As the head of the nation’s largest consortium of cybersecurity organizations and the founder of Canada’s only cybersafety foundation, he leverages his extensive credentials and expertise to drive innovation and enhance digital protection across the country. [...] As a passionate speaker and educator, Claudiu leads teams of professionals and aspiring leaders on virtual expeditions into the most exciting aspects of cyber, from the future of artificial intelligence to the most fascinating parts of the Deep Web. Whether speaking to industry leaders, law enforcement professionals, international delegations or educators, Claudiu’s talks are always immersive and captivating.

Deeply interested in the ethics of data collection and the future of information science, Claudiu is a technologist whose thought leadership is always accessible in numerous formats from his multiple books, to his numerous articles. He parlays his interest in humanitarian and animal causes into vivid examples of human achievement and technological progress. [...] Additionally, as a respected expert witness in the cybersecurity field, he is qualified to provide legal opinions and testimony, further establishing his role as a pivotal figure in promoting online safety and resilience. His unique combination of technical knowledge and legal insight makes him an invaluable resource for organizations and legal teams navigating the complexities of cybersecurity challenges.
